  "prompt": "What are the best documentary channels on youtube?",
  "response": "There are several excellent documentary channels on YouTube offering a wide range of topics and high-quality content. Some of the best include:\n\n1. **VICE** - Known for its investigative journalism and unique documentary style, covering diverse subjects from around the world.\n2. **National Geographic** - Offers content on nature, science, history, and culture with stunning visuals and informative storytelling.\n3. **TED-Ed** - Produces educational videos that often have a documentary feel, exploring fascinating topics through animations and expert interviews.\n4. **Real Stories** - Features a collection of award-winning documentaries on various subjects including crime, history, and human interest stories.\n5. **Journeyman Pictures** - Publishes cutting-edge and controversial international documentaries on politics, environmental issues, and more.\n6. **PBS NewsHour** - While primarily focused on news, it offers documentaries and deep dives on current events and social issues.\n7. **The School of Life** - Focuses on educational content related to psychology, philosophy, and emotional well-being, sometimes using documentary formats.\n8. **Freedom Archive** - Provides historical documentaries that often cover social justice movements and important historical events.\n9. **Discovery Channel** - Although known for TV, they also share documentary content on YouTube covering a range of scientific and exploratory topics.\n\nThese channels are renowned for their storytelling, investigative depth, and production quality, making them great options for anyone interested in documentaries.",
